.TH SINGINE-AUTH 1 "2026-03-13" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-auth \- authentication bootstrap and TOTP login commands
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine auth
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B auth
command provides local TOTP profile management and a login bootstrap that
verifies a code before delegating to
.BR singine-idp (1)
for session handling.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B totp init
Create a TOTP profile and optionally save it to a state file.
.TP
.B totp uri
Print the provisioning URI for 1Password or Google Authenticator.
.TP
.B totp code
Print the current one-time code for the loaded profile.
.TP
.B totp verify \fICODE\fR
Verify a submitted one-time code locally.
.TP
.B login --code \fICODE\fR
Verify a TOTP code and open a local Singine session.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.singine/auth/totp.json
Typical TOTP profile location.
.TP
.I ~/.singine/session.json
Local session state written by login flows.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine auth totp init --issuer Singine --account-name you@example.com --state ~/.singine/auth/totp.json
singine auth totp uri --state ~/.singine/auth/totp.json --json
singine auth totp code --state ~/.singine/auth/totp.json --json
singine auth totp verify --state ~/.singine/auth/totp.json 123456
singine auth login --state ~/.singine/auth/totp.json --code 123456
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1),
.BR singine-idp (1)
